","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kirkham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (mainly northwestern): habitational name from any of the places in Lancashire and East Yorkshire named Kirkham. The placenames derive from Old Norse <i>kirkja</i> ‘church’ + Old English <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’ or Old Norse <i>heim</i> ‘homestead, estate’.","Possibly an altered form of German <b>Kirchham</b>, a habitational name from either of two places called Kirchham, in Austria or Bavaria."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":8,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":81,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Kirkham was born about 1374, in Axbridge, Somerset, England as the son of Robert Kirkham. He married Agnes de Hankeford about 1405, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1374–":"umbes 1374–Surnud","1374–Male":"1374–Surnud","1379–1449":"1379–1449","1396–1451":"1396–1451","1406–1443":"1406–1443","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1451":"1451","1396":"1396","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1379":"1379","1455":"1455","about 1405":"umbes 1405","1443":"1443","about 1374":"umbes 1374","about 1396":"umbes 1396","1406":"1406","1449":"1449","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","England":"England","Merton, Devon, England":"Merton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Axbridge, Somerset, England":"Axbridge, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"about 1374–":"noin 1374–Kuollut","1374–Male":"1374–Kuollut","1379–1449":"1379–1449","1396–1451":"1396–1451","1406–1443":"1406–1443","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1451":"1451","1396":"1396","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1379":"1379","1455":"1455","about 1405":"noin 1405","1443":"1443","about 1374":"noin 1374","about 1396":"noin 1396","1406":"1406","1449":"1449","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","England":"England","Merton, Devon, England":"Merton, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Axbridge, Somerset, England":"Axbridge, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"about 1374–":"environ 1374–Décédé","1374